Abdellatif Kechiche https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdellatif_Kechiche 0 Abdellatif Kechiche (French: [abdɛlatif keʃiʃ]; Tunisian Arabic: عبد اللطيف كشيش‎, born 7 December 1960) is a Tunisian-French actor, film director and screenwriter. He made his directorial debut in 2000 with La Faute à Voltaire, which he also wrote. His film Blue Is the Warmest Colour won the Palme d'Or at the 2013 Cannes Film Festival. Abdellatif_Kechiche ( French : [_abdɛlatif_keʃiʃ_] ; Tunisian_Arabic : عبد_اللطيف_كشيش , born 7_December_1960 ) is a_Tunisian-French_actor , film_director_and_screenwriter .
